x4freetext: The method of inverse kinematics using a
very thick target
The chamber was filled with helium gas of 99.9% purity
at a pressure of 360 Torr. The beam entered a large
scattering chamber via a 3 mu-m thick Havar window.
18O ions backscattered from this foil were used to
monitor the beam intensity.
The authors gave excitation functions as function of
the excitation energy (see MISC-COL description).
Compiler calculated the energy of the incident
particle from the mass balance formula.
